      • render

        public String render(boolean isNegated,
            RenderingContext renderingContext)
        Description copied from interface: PredicateImplementor
        Form of Renderable.render(org.hibernate.jpa.criteria.compile.RenderingContext) used when the predicate is wrapped in a negated wrapper. Allows passing down the negation flag.

        Note that this form is no-op in compound (junction) predicates. The reason being that compound predicates are more complex and the negation is applied during its creation.

        Specified by:
        render in interface PredicateImplementor
        Parameters:
        isNegated - Should the predicate be negated.
        renderingContext - The context for rendering
        Returns:
        The rendered predicate fragment.
